body:
I have encountered an interesting edge case where two "simultaneous" function calls observe the same result despite being called with different inputs.

The following example:
```SystemVerilog
module top;
    reg [1:0] inp;
    wire [3:0] out;
    Foo foo(inp, out);
    initial begin
        $monitor("inp=%b out=%b", inp, out);
        inp = 0; #10;
        inp = 1; #10;
        inp = 2; #10;
        inp = 3; #10;
    end
endmodule

module Foo(inp, out);
    input wire [1:0] inp;
    output reg [3:0] out;
    always @(inp)
        out[0+:2] = pack(inp + 1);
    always @(inp)
        out[2+:2] = pack(inp + 2);
    function [1:0] pack;
        input reg [1:0] last;
        pack = last;
    endfunction
endmodule
```
Correctly produces the following output:
```
inp=00 out=1001
inp=01 out=1110
inp=10 out=0011
inp=11 out=0100
```

However, if the function is changed to:
```systemverilog
function [1:0] pack;
    input reg [1:0] last;
    begin : block_name
        pack = last;
    end
endfunction
```
The output produced is:
```
inp=00 out=1010
inp=01 out=1111
inp=10 out=0000
inp=11 out=0101
```

I am compiling and running the simulation as follows:
`iverilog test.v && ./a.out`

Version: `Icarus Verilog version 10.3 (stable) (v10_3)`

